{"key":"processedPost-11024376","value":{"id":11024376,"first":11021417,"last":11043956,"when":1252467722,"utime":"09/09/09 06:42 AM","cleanedPost":"I do up several hundred bags a month and have never owned an impulse sealer.&nbsp; I use tie wire to tie the bags shut because it gives a better seal and you don't destroy the bag getting it open.&nbsp; I use my filter patch bags at least twice.&nbsp; I've tested them up to four times, but after that they start to get brittle and I've always been worried about getting pinholes.<br />I fold the bag accordion style with a tyvek wrist sleeve inside during sterilization.&nbsp; This let's the bag 'burp' steam when needed so it doesn't explode, but then as it cools, the bag pulls tight against the tyvek, filtering the air entering so the contents remain sterile.&nbsp; You can see a demo of the process on the sawdust/woodchips page and video on my website.<br />RR"}}